Here is the implementation plan.

---

## Implementation Plan: Suggestion Pills on Empty Chat State

### Overview

Add suggestion pills to the empty chat state on `/chat` that surface governance feed items (questions, decisions, observations) as clickable entry points for starting conversations. Clicking a pill sets the discuss entity context, then the user types their message -- identical to the existing "discuss" pattern used by `GovernanceFeed` and `SearchResultCard`.

---

### 1. Component Structure

**New file: `app/src/client/components/chat/ChatSuggestionPills.tsx`**

A single stateless component that receives the governance feed and renders grouped pills.

```tsx
// app/src/client/components/chat/ChatSuggestionPills.tsx

import type { GovernanceFeedItem, GovernanceFeedResponse, EntityKind } from "../../../shared/contracts";
import { useViewState } from "../../stores/view-state";
import { entityColor, entityMutedColor } from "../graph/graph-theme";

const PILL_ENTITY_KINDS: EntityKind[] = ["question", "decision", "observation"];
const MAX_PILLS_PER_GROUP = 3;

const GROUP_LABELS: Record<string, string> = {
  question: "Open Questions",
  decision: "Pending Decisions",
  observation: "Observations",
};

export function ChatSuggestionPills({ feed }: { feed: GovernanceFeedResponse | undefined }) {
  const navigateToDiscussEntity = useViewState((s) => s.navigateToDiscussEntity);

  if (!feed) return undefined;

  // Flatten all tiers, preserving tier priority (blocking first, then review, then awareness)
  const allItems = [...feed.blocking, ...feed.review, ...feed.awareness];

  // Group by entityKind, filter to relevant kinds, limit per group
  const groups = PILL_ENTITY_KINDS
    .map((kind) => ({
      kind,
      items: allItems.filter((item) => item.entityKind === kind).slice(0, MAX_PILLS_PER_GROUP),
    }))
    .filter((group) => group.items.length > 0);

  if (groups.length === 0) return undefined;

  function handlePillClick(item: GovernanceFeedItem) {
    navigateToDiscussEntity({
      id: item.entityId,
      kind: item.entityKind,
      name: item.entityName,
      ...(item.status ? { status: item.status } : {}),
    });
  }

  return (
    <div className="chat-suggestion-pills">
      {groups.map((group) => (
        <div key={group.kind} className="chat-suggestion-group">
          <span className="chat-suggestion-group-label">{GROUP_LABELS[group.kind]}</span>
          <div className="chat-suggestion-group-items">
            {group.items.map((item) => (
              <button
                key={item.id}
                type="button"
                className="chat-suggestion-pill"
                style={{
                  borderColor: entityColor(item.entityKind),
                  background: entityMutedColor(item.entityKind),
                  color: entityColor(item.entityKind),
                }}
                onClick={() => handlePillClick(item)}
              >
                {item.entityName}
              </button>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}
```

**Where it renders in ChatPage (line ~86 of `chat-page.tsx`):**

Inside the `chat-messages` div, conditionally shown when there are no messages, onboarding is complete, and no discuss entity is already set:

```tsx
<div className="chat-messages">
  {chat.messages.length === 0
    && onboardingState === "complete"
    && !chat.discussEntity
    && !chat.conversationDiscussEntity ? (
    <ChatSuggestionPills feed={feed} />
  ) : undefined}
  {chat.messages.map((message) => (
    // ... existing message rendering
  ))}
  <div ref={messagesEndRef} />
</div>
```

---

### 2. Data Flow

The data flow is simple and reuses existing infrastructure:

1. `ChatPage` calls `useGovernanceFeed()` at the top level (unconditionally, per React rules of hooks). This starts polling `GET /api/workspaces/:workspaceId/feed` every 30 seconds.
2. The returned `feed: GovernanceFeedResponse | undefined` is passed directly to `ChatSuggestionPills`.
3. Inside `ChatSuggestionPills`, items from all three tiers (`blocking`, `review`, `awareness`) are flattened into a single array, preserving tier priority order (blocking items appear first, which means the most urgent items get selected first when limiting to `MAX_PILLS_PER_GROUP`).
4. Items are grouped by `entityKind` and filtered to the three relevant kinds.

No transformation of the data is needed beyond grouping and filtering. The `GovernanceFeedItem` type already has everything the pills need: `entityId`, `entityKind`, `entityName`, `status`.

---

### 3. Click Behavior

Clicking a pill follows the exact same pattern as the `GovernanceFeed` "discuss" action (see `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/montevideo-v1/app/src/client/components/feed/GovernanceFeed.tsx` lines 48-57) and `SearchResultCard` discuss button (see `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/montevideo-v1/app/src/client/components/search/SearchResultCard.tsx` lines 16-20):

1. Call `navigateToDiscussEntity({ id: item.entityId, kind: item.entityKind, name: item.entityName, status? })` from the `useViewState` store.
2. This sets `discussEntity` in the view state store.
3. Since we are already on `/chat`, no navigation is needed (unlike the feed/search which navigate TO `/chat`).
4. The `ChatPage` component re-renders. Two things happen:
   - The `DiscussEntityCard` appears above the chat messages (existing conditional at line 80-84).
   - The `ChatSuggestionPills` disappears because `chat.discussEntity` is now truthy (visibility condition fails).
5. The `useChatSession` hook syncs `discussEntityIdRef.current = discussEntity?.id` via its useEffect (line 77-79 of `use-chat-session.ts`).
6. User types their message and sends it.
7. The transport body function includes `discussEntityId` in the request payload.
8. Server loads entity context and generates a contextual response.
9. On `onFinish`, `clearDiscussEntity()` is called (line 111-113), removing the card.

No new wiring needed. The entire discuss-entity pipeline already exists.

---

### 4. CSS Approach

Add styles to `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/montevideo-v1/app/src/client/styles.css`, placed after the existing `chat-page` styles (after line ~1800). Follow established conventions:

```css
/* Chat suggestion pills (empty state) */

.chat-suggestion-pills {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 1rem;
  padding: 2rem 0.5rem 1rem;
  align-self: center;
  max-width: 480px;
  width: 100%;
}

.chat-suggestion-group {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.4rem;
}

.chat-suggestion-group-label {
  font-size: 0.67rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  color: var(--muted-foreground);
}

.chat-suggestion-group-items {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 0.35rem;
}

.chat-suggestion-pill {
  border: 1px solid;
  border-radius: 0;
  padding: 0.35rem 0.65rem;
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  cursor: pointer;
  max-width: 220px;
  overflow: hidden;
  text-overflow: ellipsis;
  white-space: nowrap;
}

.chat-suggestion-pill:hover {
  filter: brightness(1.2);
}
```

Key design decisions:
- **`border-radius: 0`**: Matches the project's zero-radius design system (the same value used in `entity-badge-inline`, `onboarding-action-buttons button`, `pending-file button`, etc.).
- **Entity colors applied via inline styles**: The `entityColor()` and `entityMutedColor()` functions from `graph-theme.ts` are used directly, consistent with how `EntityBadge` applies colors. Border uses the bright entity color, background uses the muted variant, text uses the bright color.
- **Group labels**: Use the same typographic treatment as `chat-message-label` (`font-size: 0.67rem`, `font-weight: 700`, `text-transform: uppercase`, `letter-spacing: 0.04em`).
- **`max-width: 220px` on pills**: Prevents long entity names from dominating; truncates with ellipsis.
- **`align-self: center` and `max-width: 480px`**: Centers the pill groups in the chat area without stretching full width.

---

### 5. Grouping Logic

Items are grouped by `entityKind` into three fixed-order groups:

| Group | entityKind | Label | Source items |
|-------|-----------|-------|-------------|
| 1 | `question` | "Open Questions" | Questions from all tiers |
| 2 | `decision` | "Pending Decisions" | Decisions from all tiers |
| 3 | `observation` | "Observations" | Observations from all tiers |

Within each group, items are ordered by tier priority (blocking first, then review, then awareness) because the flattened array is constructed as `[...feed.blocking, ...feed.review, ...feed.awareness]`. This means the most urgent items surface first.

Each group is limited to `MAX_PILLS_PER_GROUP = 3` items. Empty groups are not rendered. If all groups are empty (no items of these three kinds), the entire pills container is not rendered.

---

### 6. Edge Cases

| Scenario | Behavior |
|----------|----------|
| Feed not loaded yet (`undefined`) | `ChatSuggestionPills` returns `undefined`. Empty chat area as before. |
| Feed loaded but empty (all tiers have 0 items) | Groups array is empty. Component returns `undefined`. |
| Feed has items but none are question/decision/observation | Groups filter produces empty arrays. Component returns `undefined`. |
| User clicks a pill | Discuss entity is set. Pills disappear (condition `!chat.discussEntity` becomes false). DiscussEntityCard appears. |
| User sends a message | `chat.messages.length > 0` becomes true. Pills would be hidden by this condition too (double-gated). |
| User starts a new conversation (via sidebar) | Messages are cleared, but `activeConversationId` resets, messages reset. Pills reappear if conditions are met. |
| User navigates to `/chat` with discussEntity already set (from graph/feed) | Pills are not shown because `chat.discussEntity` is truthy. |
| Onboarding not complete | Pills are not shown because `onboardingState !== "complete"`. |
| Very long entity names | Truncated with `text-overflow: ellipsis` at 220px max-width. |
| Feed poll updates while pills are visible | React re-renders with new feed data. Groups recompute. Pills update seamlessly. |

---

### Changes Summary

| File | Action | Description |
|------|--------|-------------|
| `app/src/client/components/chat/ChatSuggestionPills.tsx` | **Create** | New component: groups feed items into clickable pills |
| `app/src/client/routes/chat-page.tsx` | **Modify** | Import `useGovernanceFeed` + `ChatSuggestionPills`; call hook; render pills in empty state |
| `app/src/client/styles.css` | **Modify** | Add ~40 lines of CSS for pills container, groups, labels, and pill buttons |

No new API endpoints. No new hooks. No new stores. No changes to shared contracts or server code.

---

### Critical Files for Implementation
- `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/montevideo-v1/app/src/client/routes/chat-page.tsx` - Host component where pills render; add hook call and conditional rendering
- `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/montevideo-v1/app/src/client/hooks/use-governance-feed.ts` - Existing hook to reuse for feed data (no changes, but must understand its return type)
- `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/montevideo-v1/app/src/client/stores/view-state.ts` - Contains `navigateToDiscussEntity` used for click handling (no changes, reference only)
- `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/montevideo-v1/app/src/client/components/graph/graph-theme.ts` - Entity color functions to import for pill styling
- `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/montevideo-v1/app/src/client/styles.css` - Add pill CSS following existing entity-color and zero-radius conventions

Here is the implementation plan.

