I see the issue. The bootstrap response includes `conversationId` and `messages`. When the workspace bootstraps, `applyWorkspace` sets the `conversationId` in the store, and `setBootstrapPayload` sets the messages. Then in `useChatSession`, the effect on line 133-142 applies the bootstrap payload:

```tsx
useEffect(() => {
    if (!bootstrapPayload || bootstrapPayload === appliedBootstrapRef.current) {
      return;
    }
    appliedBootstrapRef.current = bootstrapPayload;

    chat.setMessages(bootstrapPayload.messages as ChatUIMessage[]);


```

The effect also sets the active conversation ID from the store and updates the ref. So the bootstrap always loads the last conversation regardless of the URL — that's why navigating to `/chat` shows the previous conversation instead of starting fresh. The root cause is that the bootstrap endpoint returns the last conversation's messages, and the effect applies them unconditionally. I need to check what the server-side bootstrap route is actually returning.

